USAGES:

    <dialog type="$DIALOG_TYPE"
            title="$DIALOG_TITLE">
        (o) width="$DIALOG_WIDTH"
        (o) height="$DIALOG_HEIGHT">
       <content>
        Text goes here...
       </content>

       ... multiple <content> blocks are allowed in some dialog types
    </dialog>



    $DIALOG_TYPE        - The type of dialog:
                            0: Normal, single-paged dialog with OK button
                            1: Normal, multi-paged dialog allowing multiple
                                        <content> blocks


    $DIALOG_TITLE       - The title of the dialog, NPC name reference is allowed
                          by calling $NPC_NAME

    $DIALOG_WIDTH       - Width of dialog, in terms of grids
    $DIALOG_HEIGHT      - Height of dialog, in terms of grids